Description: Sherd of East Greek pottery dish or flat bowl with part of spool-shaped lug handle; broad flat-topped rim and flat foot minimally offset from wall; spool shaped attachments on outside for decoration. A smear of paint on the exterior lower wall (as on 1965,0930.187 and 188) is akin to marks indicating joins, though it appears ancient.
Curator's comments: Close to 1965,0930.187 and 188 but with slightly different profile.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.110)
